{"title":"Unit 4: Exercise B. Grammar.","clock":true,"countdown":0,"intro":{"buttons":{"start":"Start"},"content":[]},"activity":{"scenes":[{"block":"scene","name":"SC1","countdown":0,"instructions":{"open":true,"content":[{"block":"group","class":"flex gap-2 items-center","content":[{"block":"audio","class":"","file":"files/instruccion.mp3","wave":false,"autoplay":false,"id":"","name":"Obhs"},{"block":"text","class":"","text":"Read the information below. Then, copy the information in your English notebook.","id":"","name":"Ik0B"}]}]},"content":[{"block":"group","class":"bg-slate-100 rounded p-3 my-2 max-w-3xl mx-auto","content":[{"marker":"","class":"grid p-5 gap-5","content":[{"text":"Adjectives and Comparatives","class":"font-bold text-2xl","id":"edwG","block":"text","name":"nKWO"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* Comparative adjectives are used to establish differences between two nouns or two situations.","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S","block":"text","name":"qJdT"},{"text":"My brother is <b>older</b> than me.","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNN","block":"text","name":"udUQ"},{"text":" A motorcycle is <b>more dangerous</b> than a car.","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"xMVyc1Ow","block":"text","name":"WyZJ"},{"text":" I am feeling <b>more energetic</b> now.","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"dyqw6goT","block":"text","name":"6yjU"},{"text":" The problem keeps getting <b>bigger</b> and <b>bigger</b>.","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"VJnGnM4z","block":"text","name":"0olI"},{"text":" The <b>older</b> they get, the <b>smarter</b>they appear to be.","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"yJEjMF0v","block":"text","name":"tVNe"}],"background":"","id":"nuhg","block":"group","name":"I0GR"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* We usually add -er to one syllable words (also called \"short adjectives\").","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S1qnO","block":"text","name":"GneX"},{"text":"<b>old-older, long-longer, short- shorter</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNNbu1Q","block":"text","name":"R2R7"}],"background":"","id":"ZQd690pQ","block":"group","name":"7smU"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* If an adjective is \"short\" and ends in -e.","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S1qnOPWD2","block":"text","name":"T3He"},{"text":"<b>large-larger, nice-nicer</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNNbu1Q2TO7","block":"text","name":"WknK"}],"background":"","id":"anVDKlTM","block":"group","name":"2Q99"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* If the adjective is \"short\" and ends with a vowel and a consonant, we double the consonant.","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S1qnOPWD2venu","block":"text","name":"5QxD"},{"text":"<b>big-bigger, fat-fatter</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNNbu1Q2TO73AXf","block":"text","name":"Fu5s"}],"background":"","id":"oszsHt4X","block":"group","name":"m5oD"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* If an adjective has two syllables and it ends with -y, we must change that letter to \"i\"+ -er. ","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S1qnOPWD2venuK7Za","block":"text","name":"f9bN"},{"text":"<b>happy- happier, angry-angrier, crazy-crazier</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNNbu1Q2TO73AXf6up5","block":"text","name":"cv4A"}],"background":"","id":"iNDJZuir","block":"group","name":"mKPF"},{"marker":"","class":"grid gap-2","content":[{"text":"* If an adjective has two or more syllables, we must add \"more\" before the adjective.","class":"text-xl","id":"dq4S1qnOPWD2venuK7ZayDS2","block":"text","name":"M3Hh"},{"text":"<b>handsome- more handsome, interesting- more interesting, expensive- more expensive.</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5","id":"7qA0upNNbu1Q2TO73AXf6up51ARD","block":"text","name":"w390"},{"text":"<b>An exception to this rule is the word \"fun\" since its comparative form is \"more fun\".</b>","class":"text-xl pl-5 underline","id":"WxBM3l8N","block":"text","name":"t1VC"}],"background":"","id":"8peGo8gx","block":"group","name":"i4lP"},{"marker":"","class":"grid ga